        <abstract>
            <para>The documents on this site were last updated on
                <?dbtimestamp format="Y-m-d H:M:S"?>.</para>
            <para>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="images/C/kq_doc_1.png" format="PNG"
                        />
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </para>
            <para>This page provides links to Kubuntu documents that are
                currently under development. The documents listed in <xref
                    linkend="previews"/> are just for preview purposes and will
                be updated as development progresses. Hopefully they will be
                completed and packaged with the next release of Kubuntu. The
                main aim is to make these documents accessible to Kubuntu users
                via KHelpCenter. In addition to packaging the documents with
                Kubuntu, it may happen that they will also be displayed at the
                    <ulink url="http://www.kubuntu.org">Kubuntu Web Site</ulink>
                under the &quot;Documentation&quot; tab.</para>
        </abstract>
    </articleinfo>
    <sect1>
        <title>Call for Contributions</title>
        <para>Everyone is free to contribute to these documents. You can do so
            by giving suggestions and ideas to &quot;froud&quot; who can
            be reached at <email>sean@inwords.co.za</email> or on
            irc.freenode.net #kubuntu-devel or #ubuntu-doc. The Docbook XML
            source files for these documents are also available. They can be
            checkout from the Ubuntu Docteam Repository. <ulink
                url="http://wiki.ubuntu.com/ForTheHasty">Click here</ulink> for
            details of the repository and other Ubuntu Docteam infrastructures.</para>
        <para>Please note, if you are subscribed to the Ubuntu Documentation
            team user mailing list, that ideas and patches can also be posted
            there.</para>
    </sect1>
