    <sect1 id="devnotes">
        <title>Notes on Development Planning</title>
        <para>At UDU a <ulink url="http://udu.wiki.ubuntu.com/KubuntuRoadmap"
                >roadmap</ulink> for Kubuntu development was discussed. This
            plan serves as a basis for knowing what should be included in
            Kubuntu Documents for Breezy. However, not everything in this
            roadmap will happen. This makes knowing what will and won't be in
            Kubuntu Breezy difficult. So I will try to maintain this section
            containing items that I know will be in the release. Please note
            that it may change and that items may be added to or removed from
            the list over time. It is a good idea to ask on #kubuntu-devel if
            you are not sure.</para>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>Version of KDE</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Kubuntu will be release at the same time as Ubuntu
                        with whichever KDE desktop is available at the time.
                        Expect a 3.5.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>kbluetooth</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <application>stock install</application>,</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>kisdn</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>not sure if will be shipped</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>Qtparted</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Also not sure</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>KControl Replaced</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>KControl is replaced by kde-system settings</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>Tidy Menus</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Tidying up of applications and menu structure</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>System menu</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>System menu should be added for access to system
                        places</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
            	<term>amorok will use gstreamer</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>speak to juk</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>Home Directories</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Riddell says <quote>default folders were going to be
                            done elsewhere, I'll ask about that</quote>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>netinstall</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Riddell says <quote>kamion has promised to look in to
                            netinstall, no response on the bugzilla entry so
                        far</quote>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>package manger</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>What to do? Kynaptic or Kapture. Need to decide. This
                        also gets stuck the issue of update-manager.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>hardware database</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>ogra has promised to port to KDE</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>Graphical Installer</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>A must have or we're stuck.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </sect1>
